[hr 
]hr
[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/eien86 
		"eien86
	]a
	": In this game about police training tasks, the author reaches the highest rank "Commissioner" in just about nine and a half minutes. How's that for carreer progression?
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The movie is visibly optimized and beats the current 
	[a href=https://www.speedrun.com/policetrainer/runs/znjqol9m rel=noopener external nofollow 
		"RTA record
	]a
	" by almost 10 minutes (although that doesn't tell much since the RTA record holder has had no competition). The author shoots at targets as soon as possible, many times before they even appear. Whenever the stage allows, some extra inputs are made for entertainment purposes, which adds to the experience. As far as I can tell, the author also shoots for (pun intended) for the highest score, but it's not clear to me whether this is the absolute possible maximum.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"I was able to sync this movie using a later version of the cabinet, as I couldn't find the one used in the movie. I could not see any differences in sync or output compared to the author's encode (perhaps check the credits?)
	$LF
]div
